>  I said that using Pascal, in order to write to memory-mapped IO registers, you had to call a function written in assembly, and that in C you didn&#x27;t have to do that. I never said only C was usable that way. Please stop putting words in my mouth that I didn&#x27;t say.<p>In what language do you think the Turbo C library functions for port IO and all those handy BIOS and MS-DOS calls were written on?<p>Assembly, of course.<p>As for doing memory mapped IO with Pascal, you could something like this in Turbo Pascal. Other dialects had similar extensions.<p><pre><code>    var
       videoMem : array [0..255] of byte absolute $A0000;

    begin
      videoMem [0] := 12;
    end;</code></pre>
